Know Your Customer (“KYC”) Reliance
If you plan to use a certain Bitstamp Product or Service, it might be required that we share or receive your Personal Data with Bitstamp’s third-party providers of services (e.g. lending) or partners via which you access services provided by us. Such sharing will be made solely for the purposes of due diligence within the scope of AML requirements for the use of such a product or service. In the event you plan to conduct trading with derivates, Bitstamp Company to which you are onboarded (registered) will share required Personal Data with Bitstamp Financial Services d.o.o., which will provide you with the option of trading with derivates.
You will be notified about any such sharing before you start to use the relevant Bitstamp Product or Service in the applicable Terms of Use and will also receive a reference to that counterparty privacy notice, explaining how the counterparty will process your Personal Data as an independent Controller.
